In this codebase, always use Bun as the runtime and toolchain. Do not use Node.js, npm, pnpm, yarn, vite, or related tools.

- Use `bun dev` for all development.
- Use `bun test` for all tests instead of `jest`, `vitest`, or other runners.
- Use `bun start` for all production.
- Use `bun build <entry>` for building instead of `webpack` or `esbuild`.
- Use `bun install` for dependency management. Do not use `npm install`, `yarn install`, or `pnpm install`.
- Use `bun run <script>` for running package scripts.
- Bun loads `.env` files automatically; do not use `dotenv`.

